           SPELL=nail
         VERSION=10.4
          SOURCE=$SPELL-$VERSION.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$SPELL-$VERSION
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://omnibus.ruf.uni-freiburg.de/~gritter/archive/nail/$SOURCE
          MD5[0]=baa759a327f6c3e6b49ee3ff13313e83
   SOURCE_URL[1]=ftp://ftp.eos.hokudai.ac.jp/pub/misc/$SOURCE
   SOURCE_URL[2]=ftp://ftp.uni-koeln.de/mach/sup/$SOURCE
   SOURCE_URL[3]=ftp://download.sourcemage.org/pub/linux/distributions/sourcemage/mirror/$SOURCE
        WEB_SITE=http://omnibus.ruf.uni-freiburg.de/~gritter
         ENTERED=20020625
         UPDATED=20020625
         LICENSE=BSD
      MAINTAINER=bluebird@optushome.com.au
           SHORT="A simple command line MTA"
    MENU_ITEM[0]=${SPELL}
    MENU_EXEC[0]=${SPELL}
    MENU_DESC[0]=${SHORT}
cat << EOF

Nail is a mail user agent derived from Berkeley Mail 8.1 and contains builtin
support for MIME messages. This means it can handle international character
sets as well as attachments. In recent system environments, nail is
Unicode/UTF-8 capable. It further contains some minor enhancements like the
ability to set a From: address

EOF
